.TH "coresight_select_best_sink" 9 "coresight_select_best_sink" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
coresight_select_best_sink \- return the best sink for use as default from the two provided.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct coresight_device *" coresight_select_best_sink
.BI "(struct coresight_device *sink "  ","
.BI "int *depth "  ","
.BI "struct coresight_device *new_sink "  ","
.BI "int new_depth "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sink" 12
current best sink.
.IP "depth" 12
search depth where current sink was found.
.IP "new_sink" 12
new sink for comparison with current sink.
.IP "new_depth" 12
search depth where new sink was found.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Sinks prioritised according to coresight_dev_subtype_sink, with only
subtypes CORESIGHT_DEV_SUBTYPE_SINK_BUFFER or higher being used.

Where two sinks of equal priority are found, the sink closest to the
source is used (smallest search depth).

return \fInew_sink\fP & update \fIdepth\fP if better than \fIsink\fP, else return \fIsink\fP.
